com.guidewire.util.webservices
Class SOAPOutboundHandler

java.lang.Object
  org.apache.axis.handlers.BasicHandler
      com.guidewire.util.webservices.SOAPOutboundHandler
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, org.apache.axis.Handler
public class SOAPOutboundHandler
extends org.apache.axis.handlers.BasicHandler

Internal class used to handle outbound SOAP requests. This class is used to set the session, username, and password headers, as well as read-timeout. See the Globals class for a list of the possible values this class manages.

setHeader

public static void setHeader(java.lang.String headerName,
                             java.lang.String headerValue)
Sets the header. The headerName is the part of the header you wish to set. See the Globals class for a list of available constants. You need not enclose the constant in quotes. The headerValue is the value you are setting it to. For example:

SOAPOutboundHandler.setHeader(Globals.GW_MAX_OBJECT_RETRIEVAL_PROPERTY, "10");

Parameters:
headerName - A Globals constant defined in Guidewire's SOAP implementation.
headerValue - A String specifying the value to set.

invoke

public void invoke(org.apache.axis.MessageContext msgContext)
            throws org.apache.axis.AxisFault
Invokes the specified MessageContext. This method uses the READ_TIMEOUT property. To set the property, set it with the following prior to invoking your webservice call:

SOAPOutboundHandler. READ_TIMEOUT.set(new Integer(timeoutvalue));

If READ_TIMEOUT is not set, the application uses the org.apache.axis.Constants.DEFAULT_MESSAGE_TIMEOUT value which is 600000 milliseconds.

Parameters:
msgContext - A valid MessageContext.
Throws:
org.apache.axis.AxisFault
